<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/russia-remands-greenpeace-activists-group-appeal-070257972.html"><img src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/oaXmiJd2uyXKDuQ.zCiOHg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7Zmk9ZmlsbDtoPTg2O3E9ODU7dz0xMzA-/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/121e7e917f79b853ed0eceb50196ed77df109faf.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="A handout picture taken late on September 26, 2013, and provided by Greenpeace International shows Greenpeace International activist from Canada Paul Ruzycki standing in a defendant cage in a court in the northern Russian city of Murmansk" align="left" title="A handout picture taken late on September 26, 2013, and provided by Greenpeace International shows Greenpeace International activist from Canada Paul Ruzycki standing in a defendant cage in a court in the northern Russian city of Murmansk" border="0" /></a>Moscow (AFP) - A Russian court has remanded in custody all 30 crew members of a Greenpeace protest ship over a high seas protest against oil drilling, the group said on Friday, vowing to appeal.</p><br clear="all"/>
